Demane Pillay, left, and Sebastian Pillay leave the Port Elizabeth Magistrate&#8217;s Court Picture: Kathryn Kimberley Brothers on assault charge for injury to boy As two brothers appeared in a Port Elizabeth court yesterday on a charge of assault, the prosecution said it needed more time to consult with a young victim who was allegedly handed a lit firecracker as a prank, causing it to explode in his face. Shane Witbooi, 12, a Grade 6 pupil at Rufane Donkin Primary School in Gelvandale, was severely injured in the incident in the early hours of Sunday, January 8. Yesterday, Sebastian, 27, and Demane Pillay, 25, of Summerstrand, stood side by side in the Port Elizabeth Magistrate s Court. Demane, a marine pilot, and Sebastian, an engineer, come from a well-known Port Elizabeth family. Their mother, Penny, is a colonel in the South African Police Service, stationed at Gelvandale. Worried-looking members of the Pillay family filled the back row of the court gallery as the young men made a brief appearance. For the full story read The Herald, or get the complete newspaper, including comics, classifieds, crosswords and back editions in our e-Edition. &nbsp; Related Share on Facebook Share Share on Twitter Tweet Share on Google Plus Share